The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, July 23: A woman fell between a running train and the platform at Belghoria station this evening.

 Chutki Das, 40, lost her right hand from the wrist, superintendent of railway police (Sealdah) Barun Mallick said. 

 She was trying to hop onto the Uttar- banga Express, which was heading towards Sealdah, when she lost her footing and fell.

 Calcutta: The Left Front will meet on Wednesday to discuss the bill to relax the rural land ceiling for business and in- frastructure projects. Land minister Abdur Rezzak Mollah will meet the Assembly select committee look- ing into the bill on Tuesday to seek its approval before asking the House to extend its term.

 Burdwan: The headmaster who beat up a Class VIII student and asked him not to come to school again, driving him to attempt suicide, has expressed regret and promised to raise Rs 5,000 for his medical expenses. The labourers son was accused of stealing a classmates sunglasses. Pradosh Chandra Saha, the head of Manteswar Sagarbala Sarbarthasadhak Vidyalaya, refused to admit any wrongdoing on Sunday but wilted under pressure from the SFI, the CPM students arm.




